==English==
[[Image:Cape Triangular Postage Stamp.jpg|thumb|Cape triangle stamp]]
===Etymology===
From its shape.

===Noun phrase===
'''Cape triangle''' (''plural'': '''Cape triangle''')
#Nickname for one of several [[denomination]]s of triangular [[postage stamp]]s [[issue]]d by the [[Cape of Good Hope]] during the period 1853 - 1864.
